@notice Emitted when the owner of the factory is changed
  @param newOwner The owner after the owner was changed

@notice Emitted when the vault address is changed
  @param newVaultAddress The vault address after the address was changed

@notice Emitted when the farming address is changed
  @param newFarmingAddress The farming address after the address was changed

@notice Returns the current poolDeployerAddress
  @return The address of the poolDeployer

@dev updates tokenomics address on the factory
 @param _farmingAddress The new tokenomics contract address

natspec.details: Credit to Uniswap Labs under GPL-2.0-or-later license: https://github.com/Uniswap/v3-core/tree/main/contracts/interfaces

params.newFarmingAddress: The farming address after the address was changed

params.newOwner: The owner after the owner was changed

params.pool: The address of the created pool
params.token0: The first token of the pool by address sort order
params.token1: The second token of the pool by address sort order

params.newVaultAddress: The vault address after the address was changed

createPool(address,address).details: tokenA and tokenB may be passed in either order: token0/token1 or token1/token0. tickSpacing is retrieved  from the fee. The call will revert if the pool already exists, the fee is invalid, or the token arguments  are invalid.
createPool(address,address).notice: Creates a pool for the given two tokens and fee

params.tokenA: One of the two tokens in the desired pool
params.tokenB: The other of the two tokens in the desired pool

returns.pool: The address of the newly created pool

farmingAddress().details: Is retrieved from the pools to restrict calling certain functions not by a tokenomics contract

owner().details: Can be changed by the current owner via setOwner
owner().notice: Returns the current owner of the factory

returns._0: The address of the factory owner

poolByPair(address,address).details: tokenA and tokenB may be passed in either token0/token1 or token1/token0 order
poolByPair(address,address).notice: Returns the pool address for a given pair of tokens and a fee, or address 0 if it does not exist

params.tokenA: The contract address of either token0 or token1
params.tokenB: The contract address of the other token

setBaseFeeConfiguration(uint16,uint16,ui.details: changes coefficients for sigmoids: α / (1 + e^( (β-x) / γ)) alpha1 + alpha2 + baseFee (max possible fee) must be <= type(uint16).max gammas must be > 0
setBaseFeeConfiguration(uint16,uint16,ui.notice: Changes initial fee configuration for new pools

params.alpha1: max value of the first sigmoid
params.alpha2: max value of the second sigmoid
params.beta1: shift along the x-axis for the first sigmoid
params.beta2: shift along the x-axis for the second sigmoid
params.gamma1: horizontal stretch factor for the first sigmoid
params.gamma2: horizontal stretch factor for the second sigmoid
params.volumeBeta: shift along the x-axis for the outer volume-sigmoid
params.volumeGamma: horizontal stretch factor the outer volume-sigmoid

setFarmingAddress(address).details: updates tokenomics address on the factory

setOwner(address).details: Must be called by the current owner
setOwner(address).notice: Updates the owner of the factory

params._owner: The new owner of the factory

setVaultAddress(address).details: updates vault address on the factory

natspec.title: The interface for the Algebra Factory
